<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="50" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,768,911]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,257,807,833]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Note</emphasis>
:—This clade includes, as here defined, only a single species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nees ex Huebener" authorityYear="1834" box="[979,1108,808,833]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Jungermanniaceae" genus="Jungermannia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="sudetica">
<emphasis box="[979,1108,808,833]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">B. sudetica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and is the sister clade to the rest of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Loeske" authorityYear="1907" box="[232,400,847,872]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Anastrophyllaceae" genus="Barbilophozia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[232,400,847,872]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Barbilophozia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is treated as a separate genus (recognizing two species) by Vilnet 
<emphasis box="[1206,1265,847,872]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">et al.</emphasis>
(2009) but we do not think the genetic distance is large enough to warrant recognition at the genus level.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
